wv.text:
collision detection between two polygons
*using separating axis theorem

wx.text: assume shapes are colliding at first

wB.text: check each of shape A's normals for a gap

qW.text: check each of shape B's normals for a gap

w#.text: get support points in the normal direction

w%.text: if there is a gap, then there is a space between the shapes, so they can't be colliding

w*.text:
if the amount of penetration is less than the current minimum, then this is a new axis of least penetration 

=> set collision normal to this normal

w1.text: dot product vertex position with normal direction to calculate distance along the normal

v?.text:
sets the aabb of a shape

used once per frame right before collision detection

xd.text: distance^2 between centers of the circles

qY.text: if the distance between the centers is less than the sum of the circles radii then they are colliding

,O.text: distance between centers of the circles

,Q.text: if the distance between the centers is less than the sum of the circles radii then they are colliding

,S.text: go to the first vertex and start drawing

xe.text: only do sqrt once we are sure there is a collision - increase performance

xf.text: if the circles are in the exact same spot it will cause division by zero - if that happens then make the normal <0,1>
